In the order. The court had directed the government to consider framing some constructive mechanisms on the lines of the Central Act as per the Commission for Air Quality Management in the National Capital Region and Adjoining Areas Act, 2021 (Act 29 of 2021).

As per the orders of the Hon'ble High Court, the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority (MMRDA) has been mandated to take a multi-pronged approach and measures to address the various sources of pollution in the metropolitan area. As per the government decision of 05.02.2024, there is a twist in the formation of the coordination committee. Coordination
The reform of the committee structure was under the consideration of the government. Accordingly, the composition of this Coordination Committee is being revised as follows.
The Government's Decisions:

To control air pollution in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR) area and implement a time-bound action plan, especially during the winter months, when air pollution levels are high, for short, medium and long-term measures and implementation.
